Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a detailed summary document for you.

## Summary: OpenClaw Plugin SDK and Channel Plugin Contract

Based on my analysis of the OpenClaw repository, here's what a channel plugin must implement and understand:

### 1. **The Core Channel Plugin Type** (`src/channels/plugins/types.plugin.ts`)

The **primary export** is the `ChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>` type. This is the complete contract:

```typescript
export type ChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount = any, Probe = unknown, Audit = unknown> = {
  // Required fields
  id: ChannelId;                              // Channel identifier (e.g., "slack", "discord")
  meta: ChannelMeta;                          // User-facing metadata (label, docs, blurb)
  capabilities: ChannelCapabilities;          // Static capability flags (chatTypes, media, polls, etc.)
  config: ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount>;  // Required: account config resolution

  // Optional but commonly implemented
  configSchema?: ChannelConfigSchema;         // JSON schema + UI hints + runtime parser
  setup?: ChannelSetupAdapter;                // Account setup and name application
  pairing?: ChannelPairingAdapter;            // DM approval flow setup
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter;          // DM policy and allowlist resolution
  groups?: ChannelGroupAdapter;               // Group mention requirements and tool policies
  outbound?: ChannelOutboundAdapter;          // Send text, media, polls to platform
  threading?: ChannelThreadingAdapter;        // Reply-to mode and thread handling
  messaging?: ChannelMessagingAdapter;        // Session grammar and target resolution
  actions?: ChannelMessageActionAdapter;      // Message tool action discovery

  // Gateway and runtime
  gateway?: ChannelGatewayAdapter;            // Start/stop account connections
  auth?: ChannelAuthAdapter;                  // Login flows and action authorization
  lifecycle?: ChannelLifecycleAdapter;        // Config change and account removal hooks
  status?: ChannelStatusAdapter;              // Account status probing and diagnostics

  // Specialized capabilities
  mentions?: ChannelMentionAdapter;           // Mention stripping customization
  approvals?: ChannelApprovalAdapter;         // Approval rendering and delivery
  commands?: ChannelCommandAdapter;           // Command behavior configuration
  directory?: ChannelDirectoryAdapter;        // User/group directory lookup
  resolver?: ChannelResolverAdapter;          // Target resolution fallback
  agentPrompt?: ChannelAgentPromptAdapter;    // Message tool prompt hints
  agentTools?: ChannelAgentToolFactory | ChannelAgentTool[];  // Channel-owned tools
  streaming?: ChannelStreamingAdapter;        // Block streaming configuration
  heartbeat?: ChannelHeartbeatAdapter;        // Channel readiness checks
  conversationBindings?: ChannelConversationBindingSupport;  // Session timeout management
  allowlist?: ChannelAllowlistAdapter;        // Allowlist configuration UI
  bindings?: ChannelConfiguredBindingProvider; // Binding rule compilation
};
```

### 2. **The Config Adapter** (Required - `ChannelConfigAdapter`)

Every channel must provide account resolution:

```typescript
export type ChannelConfigAdapter<ResolvedAccount> = {
  listAccountIds: (cfg: OpenClawConfig) => string[];
  resolveAccount: (cfg: OpenClawConfig, accountId?: string | null) => ResolvedAccount;

  // Recommended optional methods
  inspectAccount?: (cfg: OpenClawConfig, accountId?: string | null) => unknown;
  defaultAccountId?: (cfg: OpenClawConfig) => string;
  isConfigured?: (account: ResolvedAccount, cfg: OpenClawConfig) => boolean | Promise<boolean>;
  unconfiguredReason?: (account: ResolvedAccount, cfg: OpenClawConfig) => string;
  describeAccount?: (account: ResolvedAccount, cfg: OpenClawConfig) => ChannelAccountSnapshot;
};
```

### 3. **The Outbound Adapter** (For Sending Messages)

```typescript
export type ChannelOutboundAdapter = {
  deliveryMode: "direct" | "gateway" | "hybrid";
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  chunker?: ((text: string, limit: number) => string[]) | null;

  // Core send functions
  sendText?: (ctx: ChannelOutboundContext) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendMedia?: (ctx: ChannelOutboundContext) => Promise<OutboundDeliveryResult>;
  sendPoll?: (ctx: ChannelPollContext) => Promise<ChannelPollResult>;

  // Advanced control
  resolveTarget?: (params) => { ok: true; to: string } | { ok: false; error: Error };
  normalizePayload?: (params) => ReplyPayload | null;
  beforeDeliverPayload?: (params) => Promise<void> | void;
};
```

### 4. **Entry Point Registration** (`defineChannelPluginEntry`)

Channels are registered via `src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`:

```typescript
export function defineChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>({
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  plugin: TPlugin;  // ChannelPlugin instance
  configSchema?: OpenClawPluginConfigSchema | (() => OpenClawPluginConfigSchema);
  setRuntime?: (runtime: PluginRuntime) => void;
  registerCliMetadata?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;  // Setup-only CLI
  registerFull?: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void;        // Runtime-only code
}): DefinedChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>
```

### 5. **Manifest Contract** (`openclaw.plugin.json`)

Required fields for a channel plugin manifest:

```json
{
  "id": "acme-chat",
  "kind": "channel",
  "channels": ["acme-chat"],
  "name": "Acme Chat",
  "description": "...",
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {
      "acme-chat": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": { /* channel-specific config */ }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 6. **Key Adapter Surfaces Explained**

| Adapter | Purpose | When Needed |
|---------|---------|-------------|
| **config** | Resolve account objects from `cfg.channels.<id>` | **Required** |
| **setup** | Account initialization and name application | Usually required |
| **configSchema** | JSON schema for config validation | Required (can be empty) |
| **security** | DM policy (`allowlist`, `allow-from`, `deny`) + allowlists | Most channels |
| **pairing** | DM approval code exchange flow | Most channels |
| **threading** | Reply-to mode (off/first/all) and thread ID resolution | Most channels |
| **outbound** | `sendText`, `sendMedia`, `sendPoll` implementations | **Required** |
| **messaging** | Session grammar, target parsing, cross-context decoration | Often required |
| **gateway** | Connect/disconnect account, maintain websocket/polling loop | Most channels |
| **status** | Probe account health, build status snapshots | Recommended |
| **actions** | Describe message tool actions and capabilities to agent | Optional |
| **directory** | List peers, groups, group members for target resolution | Optional |

### 7. **Helper Builders for Common Patterns**

The SDK provides higher-level builders to simplify common channel patterns:

```typescript
// For chat-style channels (Slack, Discord, Teams, etc.)
createChatChannelPlugin<ResolvedAccount, Probe, Audit>({
  base: {
    id: "...",
    meta: { ... },
    capabilities: { ... },
    setup: { ... }
  },
  security: { dm: { channelKey, resolvePolicy, resolveAllowFrom, ... } },
  pairing: { text: { idLabel, message, notify } },
  threading: { topLevelReplyToMode: "reply" },
  outbound: { attachedResults: { sendText, sendMedia }, base: { ... } }
})

// For a base plugin
createChannelPluginBase<ResolvedAccount>({
  id: "...",
  meta: { ... },
  setup: { resolveAccount, inspectAccount, ... }
})
```

### 8. **Types Plugins Must Export**

From `src/plugin-sdk/channel-contract.ts` — these are the **publicly contracted** channel types that plugin code can depend on:

```typescript
export type {
  BaseProbeResult,
  BaseTokenResolution,
  ChannelAgentTool,
  ChannelAccountSnapshot,
  ChannelApprovalAdapter,
  ChannelApprovalCapability,
  ChannelCommandConversationContext,
  ChannelGroupContext,
  ChannelMessageActionAdapter,
  ChannelMessageActionContext,
  ChannelMessageActionDiscoveryContext,
  ChannelMessageActionName,
  ChannelMessageToolDiscovery,
  ChannelMessageToolSchemaContribution,
  ChannelStatusIssue,
  ChannelThreadingContext,
  ChannelThreadingToolContext,
} from "../channels/plugins/types.js";
```

### 9. **Setup Entry Pattern**

Channels should export two entry points:

**`index.ts`** — Full runtime registration:
```typescript
export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "acme-chat",
  name: "Acme Chat",
  description: "...",
  plugin: acmeChatPlugin,
  registerCliMetadata(api) { /* ... */ },
  registerFull(api) { /* HTTP routes, gateway methods, etc. */ }
});
```

**`setup-entry.ts`** — Lightweight setup-only loading:
```typescript
export default defineSetupPluginEntry(acmeChatPlugin);
```

### 10. **Package.json Metadata**

```json
{
  "name": "@myorg/openclaw-acme-chat",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "module",
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "acme-chat",
      "label": "Acme Chat",
      "blurb": "Connect OpenClaw to Acme Chat."
    }
  }
}
```

### **Key Takeaways for Plugin Developers**

1. **Minimum implementation**: `id`, `meta`, `capabilities`, `config`, `outbound`, `setup`
2. **Always provide**: `configSchema` (even if empty), and manifest `openclaw.plugin.json`
3. **Common additions**: `security`, `pairing`, `threading`, `gateway`, `messaging`
4. **Use helper builders**: `createChatChannelPlugin()` and `createChannelPluginBase()` handle most wiring
5. **Entry point pattern**: Separate full runtime (`index.ts`) from setup-only (`setup-entry.ts`)
6. **Core owns**: Shared `message` tool, prompt wiring, session-key shape, generic reply dispatch
7. **Plugin owns**: Session grammar, target parsing, DM security, pairing flow, outbound delivery, reply threading, account lifecycle

The full type definitions are in the files listed at the top of your request, with comprehensive docstrings and examples in `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775501690330-dk5z6z/docs/plugins/sdk-channel-plugins.md`.

